Chief Complaint: Swelling and pain in the left foot 

History of Present Illness: John has a history of Type 2 diabetes and peripheral vascular disease. He presented to the emergency department with left foot swelling and pain that had been worsening for the past week. He reported a previous foot ulcer that had healed but the current symptoms were different. 

Physical Exam: On exam, John had erythema and warmth over the left foot and ankle, with tenderness to palpation. There was also decreased sensation in the left foot. 

Diagnostic Workup: X-ray of the left foot showed signs of osteomyelitis, with bone destruction and periosteal reaction. Blood work revealed an elevated white blood cell count and C-reactive protein. 

Diagnosis: Osteomyelitis of the left foot
